introduce new kitten into household with an established adult cat i have a female indoor two year old cat declawed in the front well tempered for the most part playful at times mellow at times fiesty too she has been the only pet i am now considering bringing home a kitten to join her thoughts suggestions is this a workable situation or will the adult cat become mean and territorial to the new addition hi honey yes this is quite workable start with a slow introduction giving your first cat almost all of the attention animal behavior scientists will tell you that when you lavish the attention on the existing pet s in a household the lst animal s do not feel their home safety is in jeopardy and they are quite willing to share the new kitty will naturally attract attention from everyone so it will not feel neglected be sure to give her lots of love and attention just not directly in front of the other kitty after about a week of early socialization they will become best friends usually the lst female will be the one to mother the new kitty best of luck to you and both your little ones how wonderful you are for taking in kitties many blessings patti Cat Socialization Kitten Feral cat Doug Ferret Azumanga Daioh Puma Pet skunk Hello Kitty Domestic rabbit Badly Drawn Kitties Attention-deficit hyperactivity disorder Aladdin (1992 film) Friends Rock Follies Mutts Hamster Cuteness Peanuts Anna Karenina Gender role Galaxy Angel Cats (musical) Marc Antony and Pussyfoot Felix the Cat Treecat Ren and Stimpy Ranma __ characters Domestic violence Shadowcat Ron Weasley Looney Tunes and Merrie Melodies filmography Animal communication Softball RuneScape quests Eric Cartman Anarchist symbolism Dog Random Harvest Lenore, the Cute Little Dead Girl Dream The Fairly OddParents Girly Pitaten Phoebe Buffay Care Bears Grief Honey and Clover Simone Weil Hearts (game) Autism Pet store Sigmund Freud Manx (cat) Mode choice Gestalt therapy Pet SpongeBob SquarePants Petplay Narcissism Tenchi Muyo!